{{see|anna}}
==English==

===Etymology===
[[Anna]] is the Greek form of the Hebrew female name [[Hannah]], meaning 'grace; gracious'. Cf. [[Johannes]], [[Hannibal]].

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ænə|-ænə]]

===Proper noun===
'''Anna'''
#{{given name|female|from Hebrew|}} A female [[given name]].

